      "id": "ADULTERANT_METFORMIN",
      "standard_name": "Metformin",
      "aliases": [
        "metformin hcl",
        "glucophage",
        "metformin hydrochloride",
        "metformin"
      ],
      "reason": "Metformin is a prescription antidiabetic drug (biguanide class) that lowers blood glucose by reducing hepatic glucose production. When found undeclared in weight-loss supplements, it can cause life-threatening lactic acidosis in users with renal impairment or who consume alcohol regularly. Users are unknowingly receiving a prescription drug requiring renal function monitoring. FDA has identified metformin as an adulterant in weight-loss and blood sugar supplement products. Any supplement containing metformin is adulterated.",
