        "7-OH-mitragynine",
        "7-hydroxymitragynine",
        "7-hydroxy-mitragynine"
      ],
      "reason": "7-Hydroxymitragynine (7-HMG) is a kratom alkaloid — and increasingly a semi-synthetic compound — with full mu-opioid receptor agonist potency estimated at 13 times greater than morphine by weight. It is responsible for most of kratom's opioid effects. FDA has cited 7-HMG as a primary driver of kratom's overdose risk. DEA designated synthetic 7-HMG as a Schedule I substance in 2024 under the Substance Use–Disorder Prevention that Promotes Opioid Recovery and Treatment (SUPPORT) Act. Products containing isolated or concentrated 7-HMG carry full opioid overdose risk.",
      "status": "banned",
