        "aristolochia manshuriensis",
        "asarum canadense",
        "guang fang ji",
        "mu tong",
        "aristolochic acid"
      ],
      "reason": "Aristolochic acids are naturally occurring nephrotoxins and carcinogens in Aristolochia plant species. They cause aristolochic acid nephropathy (AAN) — a rapidly progressive and irreversible kidney disease leading to renal failure. IARC classifies aristolochic acids as Group 1 human carcinogens (upper urinary tract urothelial carcinoma). An epidemic of AAN in Belgium in the 1990s, traced to mislabeled herbal supplements, resulted in over 100 kidney transplants. FDA issued an import alert and advisory against products containing Aristolochia, Asarum, or Bragantia species in 2001.",
      "status": "banned",
      "class_tags": [
        "permanently_banned",
        "botanical"
      ],
