        "pure cbd extract"
      ],
      "reason": "Under the FD&C Act's drug exclusion rule, CBD (cannabidiol) cannot lawfully be marketed as a dietary supplement because it was first investigated as a drug (clinical trials pre-dated any supplement marketing) and is now an approved drug ingredient in Epidiolex (approved by FDA in 2018 for epilepsy). FDA has consistently stated that CBD is excluded from the dietary supplement definition under 21 U.S.C. §321(ff)(3)(B). Despite widespread US market presence, CBD supplement products are technically unlawful. FDA has exercised enforcement discretion but this legal status remains unchanged as of 2026.",
      "status": "banned",
      "class_tags": [
        "permanently_banned",
        "cannabinoid"
      ],
