        "contaminated glp-1 compounds"
      ],
      "reason": "Compounded GLP-1 receptor agonist preparations (semaglutide, tirzepatide analogs) have faced FDA safety alerts over sterility, potency, and contamination concerns. Because GLP-1 drugs are administered by injection, any microbial contamination or mislabeling creates immediate serious risk of bloodstream infection, overdose, or anaphylaxis. FDA has warned that compounded versions using salt forms (semaglutide sodium, semaglutide acetate) are not approved alternatives. The growing market for compounded GLP-1s in supplements and online pharmacies without adequate quality oversight represents an active safety crisis.",
      "status": "high_risk",
