      "supersedes_ids": [
        "STATE_DELTA8_THC"
      ],
      "reason": "Delta-8 THC (Δ8-THC) is a psychoactive cannabinoid that occurs in trace amounts naturally in cannabis but is synthesized in commercial quantities from CBD. It produces intoxicating effects similar to delta-9 THC. FDA and DEA have both raised concerns about its legal status: synthetic delta-8 derived from hemp-CBD may constitute a controlled analog of delta-9 THC. Multiple states have explicitly banned it. FDA has received over 2,000 adverse event reports including hallucinations, vomiting, tremors, anxiety, and hospitalizations. Products are often mislabeled and accessible to minors.",
