      "entity_type": "ingredient",
      "reason": "DMBA (1,3-dimethylbutylamine, AMP Citrate) is a synthetic aliphatic amine stimulant marketed as a DMAA replacement after FDA's enforcement actions against DMAA. FDA issued warning letters in 2015 stating DMBA is not a lawful dietary ingredient and that products containing it are adulterated. Like DMAA and DMHA, it is a sympathomimetic amine that raises blood pressure and heart rate with no clinical evidence of safety or efficacy at supplement doses. It is not a dietary ingredient under 21 U.S.C. §321(ff).",
