    {
      "id": "BANNED_FASORACETAM",
      "standard_name": "Fasoracetam",
      "aliases": [
        "NS-105",
        "(5R)-5-(piperidine-1-carbonyl)pyrrolidin-2-one",
        "fasoracetam",
        "LAM-105"
      ],
      "reason": "Fasoracetam is a synthetic racetam-class compound that was investigated as a pharmaceutical for ADHD in adolescents but failed clinical trials and was never approved. Because it was investigated as a drug before any supplement marketing, it is subject to the FD&C Act's drug exclusion rule and cannot lawfully be included in dietary supplements. No NDI notification is on file. It is marketed by supplement companies as a nootropic, but its sale as a supplement is unlawful and its human safety profile is not established for long-term use.",
