      "reason": "FD&C Red No. 2 (Amaranth) was revoked by FDA in January 1976 after studies submitted to the agency raised concerns about carcinogenicity — specifically bladder and mammary tumors in animal studies, though the data were considered inconclusive by some scientists. The EU banned it (prohibited from the approved list). Despite being revoked for over 45 years in the US, Amaranth dye has occasionally been found in imported products. Any US food or supplement product containing FD&C Red No. 2 / Amaranth is non-compliant and subject to regulatory action.",
