      "reason": "Higenamine (norcoclaurine) is a beta-2 adrenergic agonist alkaloid found in multiple plants. FDA has stated that higenamine is not a lawful dietary supplement ingredient — it was first investigated as a pharmaceutical drug (cardiac stimulant), making it subject to the FD&C Act's drug exclusion rule. FDA's 2019 guidance named higenamine alongside vinpocetine as unlawfully included in supplements. WADA prohibits it in competition as a beta-2 agonist. At doses used in pre-workout supplements it elevates heart rate and blood pressure; cardiovascular adverse events have been reported.",
