      "reason": "Ibutamoren (MK-677) is a synthetic ghrelin receptor agonist and growth hormone secretagogue developed by Merck as an investigational drug for growth hormone deficiency, osteoporosis, and obesity — clinical trials were discontinued. It is not FDA-approved, not a dietary ingredient, and no NDI notification is on file. Because it was first investigated as a drug, the FD&C Act's drug exclusion rule applies. Risks at supplement doses include edema, joint pain, insulin resistance, increased appetite, and potential effects on cancer-promoting IGF-1 levels in individuals with pre-existing malignancies.",
      "status": "banned",
      "class_tags": [
        "ghrelin_agonist",
        "growth_hormone_secretagogue"
      ],
