        "igf-1 (insulin-like growth factor 1)"
      ],
      "reason": "Synthetic IGF-1 (Insulin-like Growth Factor 1) is an unapproved drug compound — not a dietary ingredient under 21 U.S.C. §321(ff). The only approved form (mecasermin, Increlex) is a prescription injectable biologic for severe primary IGF-1 deficiency. Supplement products claiming to contain 'synthetic IGF-1' or 'injectable IGF-1' are making drug claims about an unapproved compound. At supraphysiological levels, IGF-1 promotes cell proliferation and may accelerate growth of existing tumors. No safe supplement dose has been established.",
