        "hormone_analog"
      ],
      "reason": "IGF-1 LR3 (Long R3 Insulin-like Growth Factor 1) is a synthetic peptide analog of IGF-1 engineered for extended half-life (~20 hours vs. ~12 minutes for native IGF-1). It is an unapproved research compound with no human clinical trials completed and no dietary ingredient status. Its prolonged half-life amplifies cancer-promoting concerns (tumor cell proliferation via IGF receptor signaling). Any supplement claiming to contain IGF-1 LR3 is selling an unapproved synthetic drug analog. WADA prohibits IGF peptides.",
