        "iron fibers",
        "metal fiber contamination"
      ],
      "reason": "Metal fiber contamination refers to metallic particles or fibers — stainless steel, aluminum, iron — found in supplement products due to manufacturing equipment degradation. Metal fibers can lacerate the gastrointestinal tract, cause GI perforation, and lead to internal bleeding and peritonitis. FDA has issued recalls for products found to contain metal fragments, most commonly traced to broken sifting screens or worn mixing equipment during manufacturing. Detection requires specialized testing; contamination may not be visible to the consumer.",
