        "fenibut",
        "4-amino-3-phenylbutyric acid",
        "phenibut HCL",
        "noofen",
        "beta-phenyl-GABA",
        "phenibut"
      ],
      "reason": "Phenibut (β-phenyl-GABA) is a CNS depressant with GABAergic and GHB receptor activity developed in the Soviet Union as an anti-anxiety drug. FDA has not approved it and has not accepted it as a dietary ingredient. In 2019 FDA issued warning letters stating phenibut does not meet the definition of a dietary ingredient. It causes physical dependence and severe withdrawal (anxiety, insomnia, psychosis) even after short-term use at doses found in supplements. Overdose with sedatives or alcohol can be fatal. FTC and FDA have taken multiple enforcement actions against phenibut-containing products.",
