        "partially hydrogenated canola oil",
        "trans fats",
        "industrial trans fats",
        "artificial trans fats",
        "partially hydrogenated oils (phos)"
      ],
      "reason": "Partially hydrogenated oils (PHOs) are the primary dietary source of industrially produced trans fatty acids (iTFA). iTFAs raise LDL cholesterol, lower HDL cholesterol, and promote systemic inflammation — mechanisms linked to cardiovascular disease, sudden cardiac death, and stroke. FDA determined in 2015 that PHOs are not Generally Recognized as Safe (GRAS) and mandated their removal from the food supply, with full compliance required by June 18 2018. PHOs are now federally banned as food ingredients in the United States. Any current supplement product listing PHOs as an ingredient is non-compliant.",
      "status": "banned",
      "class_tags": [
        "permanently_banned",
        "food_additive_fat"
      ],
      "match_rules": {
        "exclusions": [],
