      ],
      "reason": "Picamilon is a synthetic compound formed by combining niacin with GABA, developed in the Soviet Union as a prescription drug for neurological conditions. FDA issued warning letters in 2015 confirming that picamilon does not meet the definition of a dietary ingredient under 21 U.S.C. §321(ff) — it is a synthetic chemical not found in conventional foods and was first investigated as a drug. Products containing it are adulterated. FDA requested manufacturers to stop selling picamilon-containing supplements, and several companies complied after receiving warning letters.",
