      "reason": "Aniracetam is a synthetic racetam-class nootropic compound. FDA has not approved it as a drug or accepted it as a lawful dietary supplement ingredient. It is not on the FDA GRAS list, no NDI notification has been filed, and it does not qualify as a conventional food. Supplements containing aniracetam are considered adulterated under the FD&C Act. Aniracetam is approved as a prescription drug in parts of Europe (Ampamet); selling it as a US supplement misrepresents its legal status and bypasses required drug approval.",
