      "reason": "Flmodafinil (Bisfluoromodafinil, CRL-40,940) is a synthetic difluoro analog of modafinil with greater potency. Like adrafinil, its conversion to modafinil-like activity makes it a de facto unapproved drug analog of a Schedule IV controlled substance. FDA has not approved it and has not received any NDI notification. No human clinical safety data exists. Products selling it as a supplement are adulterated. WADA prohibits its use in competition.",
