    {
      "id": "NOOTROPIC_OMBERACETAM",
      "standard_name": "Omberacetam",
      "aliases": [
        "noopept",
        "GVS-111",
        "N-phenylacetyl-L-prolylglycine ethyl ester",
        "omberacetam"
      ],
      "reason": "Omberacetam (Noopept / GVS-111) is a synthetic dipeptide designed to mimic piracetam. FDA has not approved it as a drug and has not accepted it as a dietary supplement ingredient — it is not a dietary ingredient under 21 U.S.C. §321(ff). No NDI notification is on file. It is classified as a prescription drug in Russia (where it was developed). US products marketing it as a supplement are adulterated. Psychoactive mechanism: potentiates AMPA/NMDA receptors; safety data in humans at supplement doses is absent.",
