      "reason": "Phenylpiracetam (Phenotropil) is a synthetic phenyl-substituted derivative of piracetam developed in Russia as a prescription psychostimulant. FDA has not approved it and has not accepted it as a dietary ingredient. WADA lists it as a prohibited stimulant for athletic competition. No NDI notification is on file. US supplement products containing it are adulterated and mislabeled. At pharmacological doses it produces stimulant and nootropic effects similar to controlled stimulants.",
