        "piracetam",
        "2-oxo-pyrrolidine acetamide"
      ],
      "reason": "Piracetam is a synthetic racetam-class compound used as a prescription drug in Europe and many other countries for cognitive impairment. FDA does not recognize it as a dietary ingredient and has issued warning letters to US companies selling it as a supplement. Because piracetam was first investigated as a drug and has not been marketed as a conventional food, it cannot lawfully be included in dietary supplements under the FD&C Act's drug exclusion rule. Products containing it are adulterated.",
