      ],
      "reason": "Sulbutiamine is a synthetic thiamine (vitamin B1) analog developed in Japan. Despite its structural relation to B1, FDA does not consider it a dietary ingredient — it is a synthetic modification not present in conventional foods and not covered by any NDI notification. In the EU it is classified as a prescription drug (Arcalion) for asthenia. US supplement products containing sulbutiamine are adulterated. At high doses it carries dependence and stimulant abuse potential; it is not covered by the safety record of ordinary B1 supplementation.",
