      ],
      "reason": "Vinpocetine is a synthetic derivative of the alkaloid vincamine, used as a prescription drug in Europe and Japan. In 2019 FDA issued a statement concluding that vinpocetine does not qualify as a dietary ingredient and cannot lawfully be included in dietary supplements — it was investigated as a drug before any supplement marketing. FDA additionally flagged potential fetal harm: animal studies showed decreased fetal weight and miscarriage, prompting the agency to warn that pregnant women and women of childbearing age should avoid it.",
