      "standard_name": "BPC-157",
      "aliases": [
        "body protection compound-157",
        "PL 14736",
        "healing peptide",
        "BPC 157",
        "bpc-157"
      ],
      "reason": "BPC-157 (Body Protection Compound-157) is a synthetic pentadecapeptide derived from a stomach acid-stable protein sequence. It has been studied in preclinical (animal) models for tissue repair, but no human clinical trials have been completed and no NDI notification has been filed with FDA. It is not a dietary ingredient under 21 U.S.C. §321(ff). FDA has issued warning letters and import alerts against companies selling BPC-157 as a supplement or compounded drug. Any supplement product listing BPC-157 is selling an unapproved drug compound without established human safety data.",
