        "mitragynine",
        "kratom (natural leaf)"
      ],
      "reason": "Kratom (Mitragyna speciosa) leaf contains mitragynine and related alkaloids that act as mu-opioid receptor agonists at high doses. FDA has received over 44 deaths linked to kratom use and has repeatedly warned that it is an opioid with associated addiction, dependence, withdrawal, and overdose risk. The semi-synthetic derivative 7-hydroxymitragynine (see BANNED_7_HYDROXYMITRAGYNINE) is far more potent. Liver toxicity has also been reported. FDA considers kratom to be an opioid and has repeatedly warned against its use.",
