      "reason": "Yohimbe (Pausinystalia yohimbe) bark contains yohimbine, an alpha-2 adrenergic receptor antagonist with stimulant effects. FDA has received adverse event reports of anxiety, hypertension, tachycardia, and cardiac arrhythmia from yohimbe supplements. At doses found in supplements, yohimbine can trigger dangerous blood pressure spikes in individuals with hypertension or cardiovascular disease. Drug interactions include dangerous potentiation with antidepressants, antihypertensives, and stimulants. Germany's regulatory agency (BfArM) has restricted yohimbe-containing products.",
      "status": "high_risk",
      "class_tags": [
        "high_risk_ingredients",
        "stimulant"
      ],
