      ],
      "reason": "Ligandrol (LGD-4033, VK5211) is a synthetic selective androgen receptor modulator (SARM) developed by Ligand Pharmaceuticals as an investigational drug for muscle wasting. It is not FDA-approved, not a dietary ingredient, and no NDI notification is on file. Case reports have documented drug-induced liver injury and testosterone suppression in otherwise healthy users taking doses typical of supplement use. WADA prohibits it. Supplements containing LGD-4033 are adulterated and carry serious endocrine and hepatic risks.",
