      "reason": "Ostarine (MK-2866, Enobosarm) is a synthetic selective androgen receptor modulator (SARM) developed by GTx Inc. as an investigational drug for muscle wasting and cancer cachexia. Despite Phase II/III trials, it was never approved. FDA has issued multiple warning letters about supplement products containing it. Documented risks include testosterone and LH suppression, liver enzyme elevation, and cardiovascular effects. WADA prohibits it. Products selling Ostarine as a supplement are adulterated with an unapproved drug compound.",
