      "reason": "Anabolic-androgenic steroids (AAS) are DEA Schedule III controlled substances when synthetic. When found undeclared in dietary supplements — typically muscle-building, bodybuilding, or prohormone products — users are unknowingly consuming controlled drugs without prescription. Known risks include liver damage (peliosis hepatis, cholestatic jaundice), cardiovascular effects (left ventricular hypertrophy, dyslipidemia), endocrine suppression (testicular atrophy, infertility), and psychiatric effects. FDA and DEA actively pursue supplement products found to contain undeclared AAS.",
