      ],
      "reason": "Propoxyphenylsildenafil is a synthetic sildenafil analog engineered to evade standard pharmaceutical testing while retaining PDE5 inhibitor activity. Its use in supplements is always undeclared. Like sildenafil, it carries life-threatening interaction risk with nitrates and can cause cardiovascular events. Because it is not standard sildenafil, routine FDA adulterant screening may not flag it — making it more dangerous than the parent compound from a consumer safety standpoint.",
