    {
      "id": "STIM_METHYLHEXANAMINE_ANALOGS",
      "standard_name": "Policy Watchlist: DMAA Analogs",
      "aliases": [
        "dmaa analogs",
        "1,4-dmaa",
        "1,3-dmaa analogs",
        "octodrine derivatives",
        "2-amino-6-methylheptane analogs"
      ],
      "reason": "This watchlist covers designer stimulant analogs of DMAA (1,3-dimethylamylamine), engineered to maintain sympathomimetic effects while evading DMAA's specific FDA enforcement action. Analogs include DMBA (1,3-dimethylbutylamine), DMHA (2-amino-6-methylheptane), and their structural variants. Like DMAA, these compounds raise blood pressure and heart rate and have been associated with cardiovascular events. FDA has issued warning letters covering many analogs. None are lawful dietary ingredients — products containing them are adulterated.",
