      "reason": "Cannabis and THC are prohibited by the World Anti-Doping Agency (WADA) in competition under the Prohibited List (S8 Cannabinoids). Athletes testing positive for THC metabolites above the WADA threshold (150 ng/mL urinary 11-nor-9-carboxy-THC) face potential sanctions. CBD was removed from the WADA Prohibited List in 2018, but other cannabinoids including synthetic delta-8 THC and CBN remain prohibited. Athletes using CBD supplements face contamination risk — many CBD products contain detectable levels of THC that can result in a positive doping test.",
