      "reason": "Tramadol is a prescription synthetic opioid analgesic. WADA added tramadol to the Prohibited List for in-competition use in 2024 (banned from January 1 2024) due to concerns about misuse by athletes for pain masking, its dependence and addiction potential, and an association with accidents and impaired safety in competition. Any supplement product containing undeclared tramadol is both adulterated with a prescription controlled substance and prohibited for athletes under WADA rules.",
