      "reason": "Vegetable carbon (E153) is permitted as a food colour in the EU, but the US FDA has not approved any form of carbon black as a food-colouring additive. FDA's inventories of color additives for food (21 CFR Parts 73, 74, 82) do not list E153, and regulatory and scientific reviews explicitly note that 'the USFDA has not approved the use of any type of carbon black for colouring food.' As a result, there is no approved pathway for using E153 as a colour in US foods or dietary supplements — equivalent in enforcement posture to Orange B, which is restricted to sausage casings only and effectively non-lawful as a supplement ingredient.",
