        "norfenefrine"
      ],
      "reason": "FDA has issued multiple warning letters for dietary supplements containing octopamine, stating that octopamine is a dietary ingredient under 21 U.S.C. §321(ff)(1)(F) but a new dietary ingredient (NDI) with no premarket notification on file. Because FDA has no knowledge that octopamine was marketed as a dietary ingredient before October 15 1994, and no NDI notification has been submitted, supplements containing octopamine are considered adulterated under section 402(f) of the FD&C Act. In practice, FDA uses these findings to conclude that products with octopamine 'do not appear to be lawfully included in products marketed as dietary supplements' — the same enforcement posture applied to other stimulant ingredients like higenamine and hordenine HCl.",
      "status": "watchlist",
      "class_tags": [
