      "reason": "Isopropylnorsynephrine (also marketed as deterenol) is a beta-adrenergic stimulant found in dietary supplements. Peer-reviewed analyses have documented it in weight-loss and performance products, where it can cause clinically relevant increases in heart rate and blood pressure. Deterenol is prohibited in sport by WADA and is not a lawful dietary supplement ingredient.",
